commit.message:
Reuse build-windows action for release-windows workflow:
- release-windows is now split between 2 subjobs (32 & 64 bits)
- autobuild-windows powershell script is renamed dist-windows and no longer builds the binaries, it expects them to be already built to package them for release (like it works on mac os with dmgs)
- build-windows configuration input is renamed in plural and can now be a list of configurations to build
Add release-steam-windows workflow
Build boost-iostreams without default-features for vcpkg (counter liblzma problem)
Adapt build-windows action to pass the VS configuration to it for Steam and stop calling action checkout in our custom actions to not clear the repo by mistake
Some renames from previous commit
Add bobbing option for weapon only (Blastfrog PR)

Make behind-view models have empty rects

Make models that are behind (but extend forward of) the camera have a
degenerate virtual rectangle that has just 1 base node instead of a
mirrored rectangle that breaks build_agg*_window().

Partially fixes #472.

Support object spans that extend off-map

This is a (map-) edge case for sprites, but models have virtual,
projected billboards that can easily extend off-map when close to
the camera, regardless of map position.

Partially fixes #472.
Fix broken windows CI with a temp workaround until github update their tools
Fix infinite loop in menu with music fading when audio initialization failed
Create FUNDING.yml
